{"id":60891,"title":"Teaching NeuroImages: brain mass with hilar adenopathy: the importance of histologic diagnosis.","abstract":"A 30-year-old man presented with weeks of progressive headaches, imbalance, and aphasia. Brain MRI revealed an enhancing left frontal mass (figure 1, A and B). Chest imaging revealed mediastinal and hilar adenopathy (figure 1, C and D). Metastatic cancer was initially suspected, but pulmonary lymph node aspiration revealed sarcoidosis (figure 2A). Subsequent brain biopsy revealed glioblastoma (figure 2B). ","date":"2014-05-06","categories":"Hemic and Lymphatic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24799521","annotations":[{"name":"Aphasia","weight":0.929752,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aphasia"},{"name":"Lymph node","weight":0.906012,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lymph_node"},{"name":"Sarcoidosis","weight":0.901385,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sarcoidosis"},{"name":"Lymphadenopathy","weight":0.853189,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lymphadenopathy"},{"name":"Histology","weight":0.816757,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Histology"},{"name":"Biopsy","weight":0.816757,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biopsy"},{"name":"Cancer","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer"},{"name":"Glioblastoma multiforme","weight":0.799199,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glioblastoma_multiforme"},{"name":"Magnetic resonance imaging","weight":0.790973,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnetic_resonance_imaging"},{"name":"Mediastinum","weight":0.748506,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mediastinum"},{"name":"Metastasis","weight":0.74084,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metastasis"},{"name":"Brain","weight":0.72904,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brain"},{"name":"Lung","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":